  "body": "# sync error on hdd but I am sure same command  work well in 2018 Setpember\r\n\r\nThere is some sync error, and I find a issue https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues/14381 and closed because it's fixed. But **It still appear in geth VERSION:   1.8.18-stable-58632d44**\r\n\r\nI am running two nodes(rinkeby) deploy by a sme ansible playbook, one ssd disk , one hdd disk.\r\n\r\nThis is the command which I start geth node `geth --rinkeby --syncmode=full --ws --wsaddr=\"0.0.0.0\" --wsport \"8546\" --wsorigins \"*\" --rpcvhosts {{domainHttp}} --rpc --rpccorsdomain \"*\" --rpcaddr \"0.0.0.0\" --rpcapi=\"eth,net,web3,personal\" --cache=2048`\r\n\r\nThe problem appear on the hdd disk one;  and the ssd one work well, Do I really need to upgrade hdd to ssd? But the same machine start a new rinkeby well in 2018 setember\r\n![sync_error](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/15935037/49126035-23702580-f2fd-11e8-8400-61fe70354f81.jpg)\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `geth version 1.8.18-stable-58632d44`\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n",
